This Resource describes the open state of the door. A door is
modelled by means of openState (Open/Closed), openDuration (ISO 8601
Time), and openAlarm (boolean). For Property "openState", the value
'Open' indicates the door is open. The value 'Closed' indicates the
door is closed. The type of Property "openDuration" is an RFC Time
encoded string. The Property "openAlarm" value 'true' indicates that
the open alarm is active. The openAlarm value 'false' indicates that
open alarm is not active. retrieves the state of the Door.
A string representing duration formatted as defined in ISO 8601.
P[n]Y[n]M[n]DT[0-23]H[0-59]M[0-59]S. P is mandatory, all other
elements are optional, time elements must follow a T.
The state of the door (open or closed).
The state of the door open alarm.
